  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed for primary flow outputs but inherent biological variability in the hemolysis index is assessed qualitatively for one validation result, leaving the structured UQ link absent. Full 13-factor assessment completed. Decision: Accepted.",
